author: mgrigorov
msg: WICKET-3759 Touch the page only when it is just read from the page store
Touch a page only once after it has been read from the page store - this minimizes the calls to PageAccessSynchronizer#lockPage();
Make the redirect policy for error pages AUTO_REDIRECT - this way redirect_to_buffer strategy is used and the error page is not stored in the page stores at all.
Introduce a common page for errors - AbstractErrorPage - it provides all the common settings for error pages (e.g. #isErrorPage(), #isVersioned(), etc.)
